          "thinking": "Now I have the full picture:\n\nRecord R004229:\n- employee_id: E0009 (张婷, 部门经理, 财务管理部)\n- expense_date: 2025-04-05 (expense occurred on April 5, 2025)\n- reimburse_date: 2025-07-02 (reimbursement submitted on July 2, 2025)\n- expense_type: communication\n- amount: 183.0\n- reason: \"超期报销注入样本3\" (which literally says \"overtime reimbursement injected sample 3\" - this is clearly a test data point)\n\nThe policy says: \"员工应在费用发生后60天内提交报销申请;超过期限的,原则上不得报销。\"\n\nExpense date: 2025-04-05\nReimburse date: 2025-07-02\n\nLet me calculate the days between April 5, 2025 and July 2, 2025.\n\nApril 5 to April 30 = 25 days (remaining in April)\nMay = 31 days\nJune = 30 days\nJuly 1-2 = 2 days\n\nTotal = 25 + 31 + 30 + 2 = 88 days\n\nSo it's 88 days after the expense, which exceeds the 60-day limit by 28 days.\n\nThis is clearly an anomaly - overtime reimbursement without proper justification.\n\nLet me check if there are any special approvals or exceptions:\n- The record shows `special_approval: 0`, meaning no special approval was obtained.\n\nLet me also look up the full policy document for more details on the overtime reimbursement rules.",
